          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The uranium samples were deposited as ammonium nitrate",
                "or as U3O8 on platinum discs; discs of 5 or 3.3 cm",
                "diameter and their distance from the bottom of the",
                "neutron sources varied between 3.40 cm and 1.86 cm in",
                "the various runs."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MANGB"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " For monokinetic energies photoneutron sources",
                "were selected; they were produced by power",
                "artificial gamma sources generated by Berkeley",
                "cyclotron. The total number of photoneutrons was",
                "determined by slowing them in a large bath of",
                "manganous sulphite, and a fraction of neutrons",
                "crossing the uranium sample was calculated. The",
                "neutron source was put immediately above an",
                "ionization chamber connected to a linear amplifier",
                "and containing the uranium samples to be investigated."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "From the observed count (R) the fission cross section",
                "was obtained using the formula: R = sigma x Phi x S,",
                "where sigma is the cross section in square cm, Phi is",
                "the number of neutron crossing the perpendicular to",
                "the sample per unit of time, and S is the number of",
                "uranium nuclei per square cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
